          "span": "The forward Euler method is applied to an initial value problem by advancing from the current approximation along the current vector-field slope. Its update is y_{n+1} = y_n + hF(t_n,y_n)."
        },
        {
          "lecture_id": "differential_equations_001",
          "span": "A first-order equation can be written as y'(t) = F(t,y(t))."
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "The Euler predictor is a step in Heun's method, which is an extension of the forward Euler method. The forward Euler method is applied to first-order equations, as evidenced by the update formula using F(t_n,y_n) from the first-order equation form."
